This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with person re-identification in video surveillance, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) and deep neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of metrics and loss functions, which are common topics in Multimedia (cs.MM) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
